The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) yesterday brought a Brazil returnee, Nnakeanyi Chukwuka King, before the Federal High Court sitting in Lagos for alleged cocaine smuggling. King was accused of importing 9.70 kilogrammes of cocaine into Nigeria. He was arraigned by the NDLEA before Justice Nicholas Oweibo on a two-count charge of conspiracy and illegal importation of the said illicit drug. Prosecution counsel Mr. Abu Ibrahim, alleged that the defendant was arrested with the illicit drug on March 7, 2022, during an inward clearance of passengers on an Ethiopian Airlines flight from Brazil through Addis-Ababa, Ethiopia at E-Arrival Hall of the Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Lagos.   Police arrest couple over N51m cyber fraud     Four to be hanged for murder in Rivers     Ogun PDP governorship aspirant condemns cult-relatedâ€¦   The defendant was accused of conspiring with one Onyeka, said to be at large, to commit the offence. The court heard that the alleged offences contravened Sections 14 (b) and 11(a) of the NDLEA Act, 2004. King pleaded not guilty. Justice Oweibo remanded King in the custody of the Nigerian Correctional Services (NCoS) till April 5, when his bail application will be ruled on.